item.title: China suspends imports from four abattoirs
item.description: China has suspended imports from four Australian abattoirs in an escalation of trade tensions between the two nations.

item.title: Arrest over Sydney 1988 gay-hate murder
item.description: A man has been arrested over the suspected gay-hate murder of 27-year-old Sydney-based American mathematician Scott Johnson more than three decades ago.

item.title: Compulsory virus test to protect WA police
item.description: Laws compelling infectious disease testing for anyone who exposes Western Australian police officers to bodily fluids may be expanded to include COVID-19.

item.title: Virgin Aust attracts 19 potential buyers
item.description: Virgin Australia's administrator says 19 parties interested in purchasing the airline have been granted access to a data room as of May 11.

item.title: Melbourne tunnel project jobs at risk
item.description: Hundreds of workers on the $6.7 billion Melbourne tunnel project could be sacked amid landfill cost increases.

item.title: Peters urges Maori to adapt hongi or die
item.description: Deputy Prime Minister Winston Peters has raised the spectre of the end of the iconic nose pressing Maori greeting, the hongi, due to COVID-19.

item.title: NSW premier defends cases of kids at risk
item.description: Fewer than one third of children at risk of severe harm in NSW were seen by a case worker, new figures have shown.

item.title: Man dies in SA house fire
item.description: The body of an 85-year-old South Australian man has been discovered inside a home gutted by fire in Adelaide's north.

item.title: Protesters climb Melbourne hotel roof
item.description: Protesters have climbed to the roof of a hotel in Melbourne to demand the release of asylum seekers detained in the property.

item.title: Amcor improves full year earnings outlook
item.description: Packaging provider Amcor has posted an robust increase in profits for the nine months to March 31 and raised growth in full year earnings per share.
